        <updateDate>2019-08-01T12:47:24Z</updateDate>
        <text><![CDATA[ <p><strong>Small Entity Regulatory Relief Opportunity Act of 2017</strong></p> <p>This bill amends the Communications Act of 1934 to require the Federal Communications Commission to streamline procedures for small entities&nbsp;that seek waivers from applicable regulations. A small entity includes: (1)&nbsp;a small business, small organization, or small governmental jurisdiction; and (2)&nbsp;an entity that provides&nbsp;subscription services to 2% or fewer of the consumers receiving that subscription service in the&nbsp;United States if the regulation&nbsp;waiver being sought&nbsp;applies to subscription services.&nbsp;</p>]]></text>
      </summary>
    </summaries>
